47 reasons for not completing a screening shall include those detailed in section 1 subparagraphs
48 (A) and (B).
49 SECTION 5: Upon receiving completed screening forms, all school districts shall, by
50 December 31 of each year, submit a report to the department of public health. The department of
51 public health shall create, in consultation with interested persons, an internet-based application
52 for the collection of the reports. The report shall include all of the following:
53 (1) The total number of pupils in the district, by school, who are subject to the
54 requirement to present proof of having received an oral health assessment pursuant to Section 1.
55 (2) The total number of pupils described in paragraph (1) who present proof of a
56 screening.
57 (3) The total number of pupils described in paragraph (1) who could not complete a
58 screening due to financial burden.
59 (4) The total number of pupils described in paragraph (1) who could not complete a
60 screening due to lack of access to a licensed dentist.
61 (5) The total number of pupils described in paragraph (1) who could not complete a
62 screening because their parents or legal guardians did not consent to their child receiving the
63 screening.
64 (6) The total number of pupils described in paragraph (1) who are screened and found to
65 have untreated decay.
66 (7) The total number of pupils described in paragraph (1) who did not return either the
67 screening form or the waiver request to the school.
