68 SECTION 6: The department of public health shall maintain the data described in
69 section 5 in a manner that allows the department to release it upon request. This section does not
70 prohibit any of the following:
71 (1) The department of public health from sharing aggregate data collected pursuant to
72 section 5 with other governmental agencies, philanthropic organizations, or other nonprofit
73 organizations for the purpose of data analysis.
74 (2) Use of the screening data that is compliant with the federal Health Insurance
75 Portability and Accountability Act of 1996 for the purposes of conducting research and analysis
76 on the oral health status of public school pupils in the commonwealth.
